
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes and relationships

class Person {
    +personID: int
    +phone: String
    +keywords: List<String>
    +institutionCode: int
}

class Institution {
    +institutionCode: int
    +name: String
}

class ScientificArticle {
    +doi: String
    +title: String
    * authors: List<Authorship>
}

abstract class ArticleType {}

class PeerReviewedPaper extends ArticleType {
    +citationCount: int
    * reviewers: List<Reviewer>
    +journalName: String
    +publisherName: String
}

class TechnicalReport extends ArticleType {
    +institutionCode: int
}

class Authorship {
    +position: int
    - personID: int
    - doi: String
}

class Reviewer {
    - personID: int
    - doi: String
}

class Publisher {
    +name: String
}

class Journal {
    +name: String
    +impactFactor: float
    +publisherName: String
}

' Relationships

Person "1" -- "0..*" Authorship : has
Authorship "1" -- "1" ScientificArticle : authored
ScientificArticle "1" -- "0..*" Authorship : has

Institution "1" -- "0..*" Person : employs
Institution "1" -- "0..*" TechnicalReport : publishes

PeerReviewedPaper "1" -- "0..*" Reviewer : reviewed by
Reviewer "1" -- "1" PeerReviewedPaper : reviews

PeerReviewedPaper "1" -- "1" Journal : published in
Journal "1" -- "1" Publisher : published by

TechnicalReport "1" -- "1" Institution : published by

Publisher "1" -- "0..*" Journal : has

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Person`** and **`Institution`** are uniquely identified by `personID` and `institutionCode`, respectively.
- **`ScientificArticle`** is abstracted into a base class with common properties like `doi`, `title`, and list of authors (`Authorship`).
- **`Authorship`** tracks author positions and links to both `Person` and `ScientificArticle`.
- **`PeerReviewedPaper`** is a subclass of `ArticleType` and includes citations, reviewers, journal, and publisher info.
- **`TechnicalReport`** is also an `ArticleType` and must be published by one institution.
- **`Publisher`** manages journals and can have multiple journals with the same name as other publishers.
- **`Journal`** stores impact factor and is linked to its publisher and peer-reviewed papers.
- Only **peer-reviewed papers** are published in journals (not technical reports).

